text.tspan: Cockpit lets you access and configure your server remotely.
Incoming network requests are blocked by default

flowRoot.flowPara: This allows you to use the Red Hat High Availability (previously named Red Hat Cluster Suite). Ports are opened for corosync, pcsd, pacemaker_remote, dlm and corosync-qnetd.

The Internet Message Access Protocol over SSL (IMAPs) allows a local client to access email on a remote server in a secure way. If you plan to provide a IMAP over SSL service (e.g. with dovecot), enable this option.
